title: England vs Australia, the head-to-head battle: Maggie Alphonsi rates each player... which team comes out on top?
text:
England

15. Elliot Daly (Saracens, 36 caps)

Has still not convinced everyone that he’s the best option at full-back with his defence and positioning under the high ball still an issue. Will add another gear in atack, though. 7/10

14. Anthony Watson (Bath Rugby, 39 caps)

Has looked strong and threatening with ball in hand so far. Will look at Australia’s wingers and fancy his chances going forward. 8/10

13. Henry Slade (Exeter Chiefs, 23 caps)

It’s good to see him back and his partnership with Manu Tuilagi is very exciting. If he’s fit and sharp it’s a great call, but Australia will certainly be testing out whether he is on Saturday. 8/10

12. Manu Tuilagi (Leicester Tigers, 37 caps)

So instrumental...
